-- Kenya Loses a Quarter of Its Budget to Graft, Nation Newspaper Reports
-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 2010-12-03T06:14:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-03/kenya-loses-a-quarter-of-its-budget-to-graft-nation-newspaper-reports.html
Kenya, East Africa’s biggest economy,
loses 25 percent and 30 percent of its annual budget through
corruption, the  Daily Nation  reported, citing Finance Ministry
Permanent Secretary Joseph Kinyua.  The country’s spending plan for the fiscal year ending June
30, 2011, is almost 1 trillion shillings ($12.4 billion), the
Nairobi-based newspaper reported today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Sarah McGregor  in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  